New Records: Liam Livingstone scored 87 off 47 balls, including five sixes and six fours, in his 50th T20
Key Match Events: Phil Salt walked into an apparent trap laid by Travis Head and was caught by Matthew Short
Liam Livingstone and Jacob Bethell shared 90 runs off 47 balls
Bethell's dismissal for 44 off 24 balls disrupted England
Livingstone was bowled with the scores tied and Brydon Carse was caught next ball to give Short a shock maiden professional five-wicket haul
Adil Rashid steered to backward point for the single England needed for a three-wicket win with six balls to spare
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia plundered 60 from the final five overs to finish on 193-6
England required 104 from the last 10 overs and Livingstone put the hammer down, scooping Cameron Green for six before twice depositing Stoinis into the crowd for a 27-ball fifty
The series winner will be decided on Sunday (September 15, 2024) at Old Trafford
Others: Liam Livingstone took 2-16 from three overs, and Carse impressed with a couple of wickets as he filled in for Jofra Archer, breaching 90 mph (145 kph)
